# Dry-run log — NegRisk Event Arbitrage Surfacer
# Captured 2026-05-30 against live Gina MCP at https://askgina.ai/ai/predictions/mcp
# Purpose: end-to-end revalidation of the depth-aware methodology on Gina-native tools.

# ============================================================
# STEP 1 — fetchPolymarketData (dataset=events, active=true, limit=3)
# ============================================================
$ host-tools fetchPolymarketData '{"dataset":"events","active":true,"limit":3}' --json-output-only

{
  "sql_required": true,
  "reason": "dataset_too_large",
  "table": "fetchPolymarketData_f7dfe2c8",
  "rowCount": 123,
  "columns": [
    "market_id","condition_id","slug","question","description","category","league",
    "tags","outcomes","outcome_prices","max_price","min_price","yes_price","no_price",
    "volume_24h_usd","volume_total_usd","liquidity_usd","end_date","start_date","created_at",
    "is_active","is_closed","clob_token_ids","hours_until_end","days_until_end","age_hours",
    "event_slug","event_title","image_url"
  ],
  "hint": "Data registered to SQLite table \"fetchPolymarketData_f7dfe2c8\". Use bash with sql query to analyze."
}

# Note: limit=3 returned 123 rows because each event expands to its constituent markets.
# The World Cup event alone has 60 constituent markets.
# Discovered gotcha: yes_price, volume_total_usd, is_active are stored as strings.
# Cast with CAST(x AS REAL) in SQL.

# ============================================================
# STEP 2 — Event-level sum-of-yes via SQL (the heart of step compute_event_gaps)
# ============================================================
$ sql query "SELECT event_slug, event_title, COUNT(*) AS n, ROUND(SUM(CAST(yes_price AS REAL)), 4) AS sum_yes, ROUND(SUM(CAST(volume_total_usd AS REAL))) AS ev_vol FROM fetchPolymarketData_f7dfe2c8 GROUP BY event_slug, event_title ORDER BY ev_vol DESC"

| event_slug                    | event_title                                  | n  | sum_yes | ev_vol_usd      |
|-------------------------------|----------------------------------------------|----|---------|-----------------|
| world-cup-winner              | 2026 FIFA World Cup Winner                   | 60 | 1.0190  | 1,299,314,957   |
| uefa-champions-league-winner  | UEFA Champions League Winner                 | 60 | 1.0150  |   277,212,679   |
| ucl-psg-ars-2026-05-30        | Paris Saint-Germain FC vs. Arsenal FC        |  3 | 1.0010  |    38,515,100   |

# Deviation analysis:
#   World Cup:        sum_yes - 1.0 = +0.019 → +190 bp gap                FLAG
#   UEFA CL:          sum_yes - 1.0 = +0.015 → +150 bp gap                FLAG
#   PSG vs Arsenal:   sum_yes - 1.0 = +0.001 →  +10 bp gap (efficient)    SKIP
#
# At feeBufferBp=50, two events flag. At minEventVolumeUsd=1_000_000_000, only
# world-cup-winner survives — flagship-tier exclusive surface.

# ============================================================
# STEP 3 — Pull constituent yes_tokens for the flagged event
# ============================================================
$ sql query "SELECT slug, ROUND(CAST(yes_price AS REAL),4) as yes, ROUND(CAST(volume_total_usd AS REAL)) as vol FROM fetchPolymarketData_f7dfe2c8 WHERE event_slug='world-cup-winner' ORDER BY CAST(yes_price AS REAL) DESC LIMIT 8"

